{title: Happy Christmas Day}
{artist: Charley Pride}
{composer: Written by Sue Lane and Charley Pride}

[G]Snowflakes fallin' softly quietly to the ground

Everybody knows Santa's comin' round
[C]Mistletoe and Christmas carols [G]have their part to play
But [C]they're not all it [G]takes to make a [D7]happy Christmas [G]Day

Stockings hanging by the fireplace one for you and me
Decorations red and green gifts beneath the tree
The [C]happy sound of jingle bells [G]on a one horse sleigh
But [C]that's not all it [G]takes to make a [D7]happy Christmas [G]Day
[C]Joys that swell within the hearts of [G]every little child
[D7]Thoughts of Mary and the [C]Baby Jesus meek and [G]mild
The [C]warm remembrance of our loved ones [G]that have gone away
These [C]are the things it [G]takes to make a [D7]happy Christmas [G]Day